FBIS4-27484 "dreas106_n_94005" FBIS-EAS-94-106 Daily Report 28 May 1994 Vietnam Smuggled Goods Discovered on Ship Smuggled Goods Discovered on Ship BK3105053594 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 0500 GMT 28 May 94 BK3105053594 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] Police of Ba Ria-Vung Tau recently started prosecution of a smuggling case concerning a ship, the Hoang Giang. The ship belongs to the Vietsovpetro joint venture enterprise, and was on its way back from a regular repair trip in Singapore to Vung Tau. During an administrative inspection, the customs and police forces of the province discovered a large amount of merchandise that had not been declared to customs and on which taxes had not been paid. The lot contains 22 types of items worth over 1 billion dong. This smuggling case discovered at the sea port of Vung Tau is a major one.
